<p>

<b>BeRTOS</b> is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../123/26123.xml">
real-time operating system</link> designed for <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../630/46630.xml">
embedded systems</link>.</p>
<p>

It is distributed under a modified <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../683/18938683.xml">
GPL</link> license with a special exception that grants application proprietary code the right to remain closed source while maintaining as open source BeRTOS code itself.</p>
<p>

It has a modular design, that allows to run on different architectures, ranging from tiny 8-bit <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../017/21017.xml">
microcontrollers</link> like <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../290/100290.xml">
Atmel AVR</link>, passing from <chip wordnetid="103020034" confidence="0.8">
<artifact wordnetid="100021939" confidence="0.8">
<instrumentality wordnetid="103575240" confidence="0.8">
<microprocessor wordnetid="103760310" confidence="0.8">
<conductor wordnetid="103088707" confidence="0.8">
<device wordnetid="103183080" confidence="0.8">
<semiconductor_device wordnetid="104171831" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../558/60558.xml">
ARM architecture</link></semiconductor_device>
</device>
</conductor>
</microprocessor>
</instrumentality>
</artifact>
</chip>
 and arriving to <O wordnetid="106832680" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../297/6097297.xml">
Linux</link></O>
 and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../890/18890.xml">
Microsoft Windows</link> hosted applications.</p>
<p>

BeRTOS' <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../857/6857.xml">
multitasking</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../394/50394.xml">
kernel</link> implements some <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../106/152106.xml">
 IPC</link> primitives like:
<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../602/938602.xml">
Signals</link></entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../557/164557.xml">
Semaphores</link></entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../867/1324867.xml">
Messages</link></entry>
</list>
</p>
<p>

In addition to the kernel, BeRTOS has several generic peripheral drivers (timer, serial, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../367/40367.xml">
ADC</link>, motors, LCD display, NTC sensors, keyboard, buzzer, memories), algorithms (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../833/13833.xml">
hash table</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../838/38838.xml">
CRC</link>, <function wordnetid="113783816" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../819/1044819.xml">
MD2</link></function>
, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../506/160506.xml">
entropy pool</link>, <event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<rule wordnetid="105846932" confidence="0.8">
<act wordnetid="100030358" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<procedure wordnetid="101023820" confidence="0.8">
<activity wordnetid="100407535" confidence="0.8">
<algorithm wordnetid="105847438" confidence="0.8">
